parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission, specifically in 2nd gear, can cause the motorcycle to lose power, slip out of gear, or jump into neutral, leading to accidents, near-misses, and a high risk of rear-ending or being rear-ended.
symptoms: The motorcycle slips out of 2nd gear
jumps into neutral
has a grinding noise when shifting into 2nd gear
has difficulty shifting into 2nd gear
or has a shuttering or violent shuttering when accelerating from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the motorcycle to stutter, slip, or shutter, leading to accidents, near-misses, and a high risk of rear-ending or being rear-ended.
symptoms: The clutch shudders or slips when accelerating from a stop
has a grinding noise when shifting into gear
or has difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Defect Leading to Stalling and Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system defect can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, potentially leading to a fire, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the vehicle catches on fire
difficulty accelerating
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair Due to Part Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can lead to extended delays, leaving vehicles with known safety defects on the road, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are unavailable
extended wait times for repair
vehicle remains in unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear brake pad from its housing can cause a loss of rear brake stopping power, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear wheel binds or drags when spun in reverse
the inside brake pad protrudes out from between the brake pad housing and the brake rotor
the brake pad can be pulled out of the housing by hand
loss of rear brake stopping power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pad housing can cause the brake pad to separate, leading to a loss of rear brake stopping power, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear wheel binds or drags when spun in reverse
the inside brake pad protrudes out from between the brake pad housing and the brake rotor
the brake pad can be pulled out of the housing by hand
loss of rear brake stopping power.
